Southern and Middle Belt Leaders Forum (SMBLF) has appointed Chief John Nwodo as national co­ordinator. This was contained in a state­ment issued by the Chairman of the forum, Chief Edwin Clarke, on Wednesday. Clarke said that Nwodo, the outgoing President-General of the Ohanaeze Ndigbo Worldwide ap­pointment, took effect from Janu­ary 10, ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He said Nwodo’s appointment was in recognition of his superla­tive four-year leadership of the apex Igbo socio-cultural organisation. The chairman also said that the appointment was based on the man­ifest role Nwodo had been playing in the affairs of the forum. Bullish Momentum Returns As Equities Market Gains 0.17% COVID-19 Investigations: WHO Blasts China For Blocking Team From Entering Country He said that Nwodo gave the Igbo purposeful leadership which reso­nated throughout the country. “We are optimistic that he will do the same for the Southern and Middle Belt Leaders Forum,’’ he said. Clarke urged Nwodo to bring his wealth of knowledge and expe­rience to bear on the new job; which entails coordinating the affairs of the forum and carrying out all lead­ership assignments. “Chief Nwodo’s appointment takes effect from Jan. 10, 2021, the same day his tenure as Ohanaeze Ndigbo President-General ends,’’ he said. The forum is made up of Afenifere, PANDEF, Ohanaeze Ndig­bo and Middle Belt Forum.